FBIS4-38067 "drnes124_l_94018" FBIS-NES-94-124 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 ISRAEL Reports on Incidents of Violence Continue Reports on Incidents of Violence Continue Arab Shot Dead in Nabulus TA2406163394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 24 Jun 94 TA2406163394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] An Arab youth was shot and killed during a riot in Nabulus at noon following a demonstration demanding the release of all Palestinian prisoners. Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that there were similar demonstrations in other towns in the territories, and in Gaza and Jericho in the autonomy. In Gaza, thousands today attended the funeral of Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] activist Nasir Faluha, who was murdered yesterday. The Palestinian police safeguarded the funeral procession. During the funeral ceremony there were calls to kill Faluha's murderer. Our correspondent Nisim Qeynan notes that the Palestinian police detained a suspect, 'Abd-al-Salam 'Alwan, a brother of a collaborator murdered several months ago by Hamas' 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam military arm.
